{
  "format": "legion",
  "format_version": 1,
  "metadata": {
    "title": "finetune-llama-lora.legion",
    "kernel": { "name": "python3", "display_name": "Python 3", "language": "python" },
    "sandbox": "local",
    "created_at": "2026-06-21T10:00:00.000Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-06-21T10:06:00.000Z",
    "legion_version": "0.3.0",
    "extensions": {}
  },
  "cells": [
    {
      "id": "cell-intro",
      "kind": "markdown",
      "source": "# Fine-tune Llama-3.1-8B with QLoRA\n\n**QLoRA** (Quantized Low-Rank Adaptation) reduces optimizer memory by ~75% so you can fine-tune a 7-8B model on a single 24 GB GPU. This notebook fine-tunes Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct on a small instruction dataset using PEFT + bitsandbytes 4-bit quantization.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n```bash\npip install transformers peft trl bitsandbytes accelerate datasets torch\n```\n\n## Notes\n\n- Model: `meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct` (gated).\n- Dataset: `tatsu-lab/alpaca` (52k instruction pairs).\n- ~22 GB VRAM at 4-bit + LoRA rank 16. LoRA adapter weights are ~50 MB.",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "id": "cell-imports",
      "kind": "code",
      "source": "import torch\nfrom datasets import load_dataset\nfrom transformers import (\n    AutoModelForCausalLM,\n    AutoTokenizer,\n    BitsAndBytesConfig,\n    TrainingArguments,\n)\nfrom peft import LoraConfig, get_peft_model, prepare_model_for_kbit_training\nfrom trl import SFTTrainer\n\nMODEL_ID = \"meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct\"\nprint(\"cuda:\", torch.cuda.is_available())",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "id": "cell-data",
      "kind": "code",
      "source": "# Load a small slice of Alpaca to keep training time bounded for the demo.\nds = load_dataset(\"tatsu-lab/alpaca\", split=\"train[:2000]\")\nprint(\"train samples:\", len(ds))\nprint(\"sample:\", ds[0][\"instruction\"][:80])",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "id": "cell-format",
      "kind": "code",
      "source": "# Format each example as a chat-turn string the model can learn.\ntokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(MODEL_ID)\nif tokenizer.pad_token is None:\n    tokenizer.pad_token = tokenizer.eos_token\n\ndef fmt(example):\n    instr = example[\"instruction\"].strip()\n    inp = (example[\"input\"] or \"\").strip()\n    out = example[\"output\"].strip()\n    user = instr + (f\"\\n{inp}\" if inp else \"\")\n    msgs = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": out}]\n    return {\"text\": tokenizer.apply_chat_template(msgs, tokenize=False)}\n\nds = ds.map(fmt, remove_columns=ds.column_names)\nprint(ds[0][\"text\"][:300])",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "id": "cell-quant",
      "kind": "code",
      "source": "# 4-bit quantization config — NF4 with double-quantization for memory savings.\nbnb_config = BitsAndBytesConfig(\n    load_in_4bit=True,\n    bnb_4bit_quant_type=\"nf4\",\n    bnb_4bit_compute_dtype=torch.float16,\n    bnb_4bit_use_double_quant=True,\n)\n\nmodel = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\n    MODEL_ID,\n    quantization_config=bnb_config,\n    device_map=\"auto\",\n)\nmodel = prepare_model_for_kbit_training(model)\nprint(\"model loaded in 4-bit. trainable params before LoRA:\",\n      sum(p.numel() for p in model.parameters() if p.requires_grad))",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "id": "cell-lora",
      "kind": "code",
      "source": "# Attach LoRA adapters to the attention + MLP projections.\nlora_config = LoraConfig(\n    r=16,\n    lora_alpha=32,\n    lora_dropout=0.05,\n    bias=\"none\",\n    task_type=\"CAUSAL_LM\",\n    target_modules=[\"q_proj\", \"k_proj\", \"v_proj\", \"o_proj\",\n                    \"gate_proj\", \"up_proj\", \"down_proj\"],\n)\n\nmodel = get_peft_model(model, lora_config)\nmodel.print_trainable_parameters()",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "id": "cell-train-args",
      "kind": "code",
      "source": "# TrainingArguments — small batch + grad accumulation to fit 24 GB VRAM.\ntraining_args = TrainingArguments(\n    output_dir=\"./llama3-lora-out\",\n    per_device_train_batch_size=2,\n    gradient_accumulation_steps=4,\n    learning_rate=2e-4,\n    lr_scheduler_type=\"cosine\",\n    warmup_ratio=0.03,\n    num_train_epochs=1,\n    logging_steps=10,\n    save_strategy=\"epoch\",\n    bf16=torch.cuda.is_bf16_supported(),\n    fp16=not torch.cuda.is_bf16_supported(),\n    optim=\"paged_adamw_8bit\",\n    report_to=\"none\",\n    seed=42,\n)\nprint(\"training args ready.\")",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "id": "cell-train",
      "kind": "code",
      "source": "# Launch SFTTrainer — this runs the actual fine-tune. Expect ~10 min on an A100 for 2k samples x 1 epoch.\ntrainer = SFTTrainer(\n    model=model,\n    args=training_args,\n    train_dataset=ds,\n    tokenizer=tokenizer,\n    max_seq_length=1024,\n    packing=False,\n)\n\ntrainer.train()\nprint(\"training complete.\")",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "id": "cell-save",
      "kind": "code",
      "source": "# Save just the LoRA adapter (~50 MB).\nadapter_dir = \"./llama3-lora-adapter\"\nmodel.save_pretrained(adapter_dir)\ntokenizer.save_pretrained(adapter_dir)\nprint(\"saved adapter to\", adapter_dir)\n\nimport os\nfor f in os.listdir(adapter_dir):\n    sz = os.path.getsize(os.path.join(adapter_dir, f))\n    print(f\"  {f}: {sz/1024:.1f} KB\")",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "id": "cell-test",
      "kind": "code",
      "source": "# Quick sanity check — generate from the fine-tuned model.\nprompt = tokenizer.apply_chat_template(\n    [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"List 3 healthy breakfast ideas.\"}],\n    tokenize=False, add_generation_prompt=True,\n)\ninputs = tokenizer(prompt, return_tensors=\"pt\").to(model.device)\nwith torch.inference_mode():\n    out = model.generate(**inputs, max_new_tokens=120, do_sample=True,\n                         temperature=0.7, top_p=0.9)\nprint(tokenizer.decode(out[0, inputs[\"input_ids\"].shape[1]:], skip_special_tokens=True))",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "id": "cell-merge",
      "kind": "markdown",
      "source": "## Merging the adapter (optional)\n\nFor deployment you usually merge the LoRA weights back into the base model and save a single fp16 checkpoint:\n\n```python\nfrom peft import PeftModel\nbase = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(MODEL_ID, torch_dtype=torch.float16)\nmerged = PeftModel.from_pretrained(base, adapter_dir).merge_and_unload()\nmerged.save_pretrained(\"./llama3-lora-merged\")\n```\n\nThe merged model can then be served with vLLM / TGI / `transformers` like any other checkpoint.",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    }
  ]
}
